The multinational joint task force in the Lake Chad basin has disclosed the interception of many bicycles near the borders of Sambisa Forest meant for supply to terrorists in northeast Nigeria.

The chains of bicycles include 21 new bicycles, as well as other items which include substances suspected to be cannabis, being ferried in a convoy of terrorists’ vehicles, were obstructed by the MNJTF troops at the Vretet-Zamga-Ngoshe triangle in the region of Kirawa on the Nigeria/Cameroon borders. The multinational task force confiscated the bicycles and others items from the dealers.







